    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The underground spheroidal portions of the stem of certain plants, such as an onion, lily, or other plant of analogous mode of growth. Although in popular language regarded as a kind of ‘root,’ bulbs are not roots.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
